dismissalText.commentary: David Warner lbw b Santner 98 (79b 8x4 4x6 120m) SR: 124.05

dismissalComment.html: big appeal for lbw, not given by ump Billy. Did the pitch outside leg? Baz, Ronchi, and Santner have a chat. Santner coaxes his captain to review it. Arrowed in from round the wicket, strikes the back pad. No inside edge involved. Pitched in line, the tracker shows that it would smash the middle of middle stump. No century for Warner. Game-changing incision from Santner?

dismissalComment.html: fifty and out! Chipped back to the bowler off a leading edge. Drifting into the pads again, Khawaja targets the leg side with a gentle little flick. He can only spoon a return catch to Santner who breaks the rousing opening partnership

It soars over for a six Milne pulls off a stunning one-handed catch at the edge of the midwicket boundary (allow me to pick up my jaw from the floor). Milne does a Vettori.Wade can't believe this. He drops to his knees. Pushed through short on middle, Wade skips back and nails a pull. It looks destined to go for a six. But Milne takes flight, times his jump to perfection, and comes out with the ball in his left hand. It took some time for the crowd and Milne himself to realise that he had plucked it!

commentTextItems.html: Hastings is pumped. Marsh embraces him. Hastings finishes it off with successive fours. Near half-volley length, blugeoned ram-rod straight down the ground. Has Hastings snatched the finishing rights from Faulkner?

commentPostTextItems.html: 9:30pm Australia bounce back to level the series. After the lower order rallied NZ to 281 for 9, Warner and Khawaja gave Australia a rousing start with an 122-run partnership. Though the visitors' middle order fell away, Mitch Marsh stepped up, as did John Hastings in an unbroken 86-run partnership under pressure.

New Zealand's fielding was superb, exemplified by catches from Milne and Ronchi. Baz kept attacking Australia. He even deployed a slip to a set Warner who was batting in the nineties. Marsh was then welcomed by a two-man slip cordon. New Zealand willed themselves to manufacture a win, but they were overpowered by Marsh. Hastings played some smart cricket as well, finding the gaps before launching some big hits at the end.
Marsh and Hastings had a good day at the IPL auction as well

Baz: I thought we were okay. We were par. That summed up the game, we were just okay. Australia played well under pressure. We are still learning a little bit. We are still hanging in there. Santner is a gun cricketer. He is a huge positive for us. I thought the bowlers did d good job as well. Australia took their opportunities and deserve to win. We had another big crowd today; I'm sure there will be a bumper crowd at Hamilton. It should be a cracker

Smith: I thought the way we were able to scrape over the line, we showed composure. We could have bowled them out for 250. We let it slip, I dropped a catch. I thought the surface was pretty good and I'm just pleased we were able to scrape home. Hastings did a terrific job. No.3,4, and 5 still have a lot of work to do. Zampa did well, he took crucial two wickets.
Mitch Marsh is the Man of the Match
Santner: Warner played fantastically.That brought us back into the game. Milne's catch was pretty good from my angle. It was an awesome catch at a crucial time.
Vishaal : "How good has the Big Duke been for Australia today!! "
Andrew : "Haven't been a Hastings fan til now, but he's changing my mind!"
Pranav: "Hastings did the Faulkner at wellington. "
That is all we have for you from this match. It was good fun bringing this to you. Do tune in for the decider at Seddon Park as well, on Monday. Cheers and ta ta!

commentTextItems.html: hint of width outside off, flat-bat belt past mid-off, Hastings sends it thudding to the boundary
Boult nails a yorker on middle and leg, squirted out to mid-off
full and outside off, another slower one, 120ks, Marsh yanks his bottom hand off the bat and squeezes it to point

commentPostTextItems.html: Rohit Verma: "Thanks to M Marsh for reminding me how proud Australian fans used to feel when the two other M's Michael Bewan and Michael Hussey used to do the same almost every time they needed to!! "

headshotImage.longCaption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentPreTextItems.html: Burhan: "Welcome to KKR Hastings, the knock itself shows you richly deserved it :)"

commentTextItems.html: short, tucks Marsh up for room on the off stump. Back of the hand slower ball, chopped towards cover

commentPreTextItems.html: Manu: "Maybe after this innings M Marsh can boast about his batting average at family dinners"

commentTextItems.html: full on the stumps, pushed to mid-on
short on leg, Hastings skips away again, dabbed down to third man

commentPostTextItems.html: Abdul Rasheed: "Hastings is today's unsung hero, he bowled magnificently well, was economical with ball and handy with bat."

commentPreTextItems.html: Baz moves to leg gully. Milne from round the stumps

commentTextItems.html: bouncer outside off, Hastings throws his hands. Flashes and misses
Hastings backs away outside leg, the bowler errs in length. The low full toss is tonked over midwicket. It exploded from the meat of the bat
low full toss, Hastings goes for a leg-side flick and chips it just in front of Baz at short cover. ''He won't give up," says Ian Smith

commentTextItems.html: full on off, square-driven for one

commentPostTextItems.html: RD Podder: "Marsh is today's hero for Australia.He played a brilliant knock."

commentPreTextItems.html: Mitch Marsh needs some taping on the bottom of his bat. Shaun Marsh is out, taping his brother's bat.

commentTextItems.html: back of a length on off, punched down the ground, but Corey Anderson moves swift to his right at mid-off and cuts it off
full and aimed at the base of off, slapped to mid-off, Anderson throws himself to his right and keeps it to a dot
slippery bouncer, soars over the batsman to Ronchi. Ump Billy calls it a wide
low full toss, mis-hit to mid-off, diving stop
short and ducks in with the angle. Hastings sways back and away as he rides it down to third man
Henry ends the over with another slower ball, flat-batted to mid-off

commentPostTextItems.html: Mujeeb: "A wicket here will make the things interesting........,!" --- I guess Aus have the game in the bag

headshotImage.longCaption: Henry Nicholls player page headshot cutout, 2021

He bowled a short and wide ball outside off from around the wicket, with a cross seam so it gripped the pitch a bit. It might have been called wide had Nichollls let it go but he chased it with a half-hearted waft at edged through to Wade. If you're going to slash, slash hard ...

headshotImage.longCaption: Scott Boland player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brendon McCullum b Boland 28 (12b 2x4 3x6 18m) SR: 233.33

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! What a lift for Boland! McCullum charged him again but this time the length was not full and McCullum's swing connected with nothing, Boland hit the top of off stump. The fans at the Cake Tin rise to give McCullum a cheer as he walks off

headshotImage.caption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill c Khawaja b Marsh 31 (45b 4x4 0x6 64m) SR: 68.88

dismissalComment.html: caught at deep cover! Guptill came out of his crease and moved towards leg to smash a good length ball from outside off down the ground, the bat turned in his hand as he made contact and he ended up slicing the ball towards the cover boundary, where Khawaja settled under the catch. He judged that well, because the ball seemed to be swirling and it wasn't straightforward

headshotImage.longCaption: Henry Nicholls player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Henry Nicholls player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Henry Nicholls player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Henry Nicholls c †Wade b Marsh 4 (5b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 80

dismissalComment.html: that's a loose ball and a loose shot and a loose dismissal, Marsh is thrilled with his second wicket. It might have been called wide had Nichollls let it go but he chased it with a half-hearted waft at edged through to Wade. If you're going to slash, slash hard ...

headshotImage.caption: Adam Zampa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adam Zampa player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson c Smith b Zampa 60 (74b 5x4 1x6 100m) SR: 81.08

dismissalComment.html: KW can't hit the repeat button, Zampa celebrates his maiden ODI wicket. Nicely lobbed up outside off, KW drives in the air again, this time he picks out Smith at extra-cover. Big, big wicket. KW spins his head away in disappointment

headshotImage.caption: Adam Zampa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adam Zampa player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Grant Elliott c Maxwell b Zampa 32 (47b 2x4 1x6 53m) SR: 68.08

dismissalComment.html: Elliott does a KW. Zampa gives this loads of air, tempts Elliott into an airy stroke. The ball dips, and the batsman drives it in the air.... into the lap of Maxi who takes it calmly despite a little juggle. Two in two for the debutant

headshotImage.caption: Scott Boland player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Scott Boland player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Luke Ronchi c Marsh b Boland 19 (19b 0x4 1x6 20m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: another soft dismissal, another failure for Ronchi. Back of a length, Ronchi may have misjudged the pace on this. The back-of-a-length ball stopped on him as he shaped to flick. He can only chip it to Mitch Marsh at mid-on; chest-high catch

dismissalText.commentary: Corey Anderson c †Wade b Hazlewood 16 (28b 0x4 1x6 46m) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: he comes back and takes down Anderson. Full and swerves away with the angle outside off. Anderson does not want to hold back. He throws his bat at it. He can only settle with a thin tickle behind to Wade. NZ are falling away

dismissalText.commentary: Adam Milne c Smith b Hazlewood 36 (27b 2x4 1x6 32m) SR: 133.33

dismissalComment.html: well, that was simple! Fierecly struck but straight down the throat of the Australian captain. End of a sparky cameo from Milne. He dances out to a length ball and drills it to Smith at cover

headshotImage.caption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Matt Henry b Hazlewood 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: knocked him over. The middle stump is flattened. Back of a length, straight on middle, Henry clears his front leg. Goes for a wild, dirty slog, and misses. Hazlewood pounds the middle stump

headshotImage.caption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Usman Khawaja c & b Santner 50 (49b 7x4 0x6 59m) SR: 102.04

dismissalComment.html: fifty and out! Chipped back to the bowler off a leading edge. Drifting into the pads again, Khawaja targets the leg side with a gentle little flick. He can only spoon a return catch to Santner who breaks the rousing opening partnership

headshotImage.caption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner lbw b Santner 98 (79b 8x4 4x6 120m) SR: 124.05

dismissalComment.html: big appeal for lbw, not given by ump Billy. Did the pitch outside leg? Baz, Ronchi, and Santner have a chat. Santner coaxes his captain to review it. Arrowed in from round the wicket, strikes the back pad. No inside edge involved. Pitched in line, the tracker shows that it would smash the middle of middle stump. No century for Warner. Game-changing incision from Santner?

headshotImage.caption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Steven Smith c †Ronchi b Henry 2 (12b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: this wasn't crunched. This was just edged. Cracker of a stop followed by a cracker of a  catch. Full and outside off, Smith feels for the ball and outside-edges it towards first slip. But Ronchi dives full-stretch to his right and snaps up the one-handed catch. Ronchi may have lost it with the bat, but he still has it with the gloves

headshotImage.caption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey b Henry 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: double-blow from Henry! He lets out a massive roar. Bailey is gone for a golden duck. He went unsold in the IPL auction as well. This is a gem. Back of a length, snakes back in a long way off the seam. Rips through the gate and hits the top of off

dismissalText.commentary: Glenn Maxwell b Boult 6 (10b 1x4 0x6 13m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: Boult has Maxi chopping on. Boult flashes a smile. Fractionally short, not much room either, Maxi shapes to pull. He gets a thick inside edge that rebounds off pad and hits the furniture

dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Marsh not out 69 (72b 9x4 1x6 110m) SR: 95.83

headshotImage.caption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Matthew Wade c Milne b Santner 2 (9b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 22.22

dismissalComment.html: It soars over for a six Milne pulls off a stunning one-handed catch at the edge of the midwicket boundary (allow me to pick up my jaw from the floor). Milne does a Vettori.Wade can't believe this. He drops to his knees. Pushed through short on middle, Wade skips back and nails a pull. It looks destined to go for a six. But Milne takes flight, times his jump to perfection, and comes out with the ball in his left hand. It took some time for the crowd and Milne himself to realise that he had plucked it!
